In news overseas , at a United Nations environmental summit in Johannesburg , South Africa , representatives from 122 nations signed an agreement banning the use of <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">12 highly toxic chemicals</COREF> .
Among <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">them</COREF> , dioxins and other chemicals , which are known as `` the Dirty Dozen . ''
<COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">They</COREF> have been linked to cancer , birth defects , and other genetic abnormalities .
